message:
Externalize dependecies
This allows for better composibility and flexibility
Remove bind syntax for simple fn, add tests
Add flow hook in Sinuous h
Change sinuous function signature and cleanup

Remove local bench
Will keep this in its own repo

Prevent using cache for hugo
Fixes showing the old Sinuous version

Prevent prettier on htm packages
Keep it easy to see diff from the original developit/htm

Fix mixed exports
It's not recommended to have a default AND named exports

Add handling of non-node, non-array in root
Fixes #22. This makes the `html` tag always return an instance of Node

Replace Sinon w/ ispy
Sinon is too big

Use `Map` in map again
Related issue #23. It's not worth the hassle and it was broken.
Add support for web ES modules fixes #27
Add cellx performance test w/ Sinuous observable
Add persistent travis bench results, start v0.12.6
Add better support for adjacent text nodes
Add Node tape tests for the `htm` module
Add better karma and tap logging

Fix a treeshake issue #76
Unused observable functions were not removed.
Hello world went from 1.6kB to 1.4kB 🏌️‍♂️
Using symlinks to point Sinuous to itself in node_modules
Add new map based on list-difference
Cleanup Rollup script, update Babel, and show ESM/UDM/etc while building

Revert to old map diff algo
It has better performance for a small increase in size
ci: fix Chrome Karma hanging, replace w/ Firefox

feat: remove `data` package
don't think this is used, this is part of simplifying the library

feat: remove `all` package
part of simplifying the lib
chore: exclude test folders in publish

fix: set ES module flag in package.json

NodeJS requires `"type": "module"` in package.json in order to be
considered a valid ES module. This is required for isomorphic apps
using sinuous on both server and client.
fix: karma to still use cjs
